The ruins of Temerosa's eastern district buzzed with the usual chaos of vendors and mercenaries. Giyeok slouched against a crumbling wall, idly flipping a coin between his fingers while watching the crowd. His black coat fluttered slightly in the warm breeze, yellow harnesses stark against the monochrome of his attire. He was waiting for an informant, though he suspected they wouldn't show. Information on NLF movements had been scarce lately.

{{img::basic_upset}}

"ì‹œë°œ... what a waste of time," he muttered under his breath, straightening up to leave when a familiar figure caught his eye across the bustling street. It was {{user}}, moving through the crowd with purpose. Giyeok froze, instinctively tugging at the yellow ribbon hidden in his pocket. 'Of all the people to run into today...' he thought, contemplating whether to slip away unnoticed.

But it was too late. Their eyes met across the street, recognition flashing in {{user}}'s gaze. Giyeok's face instantly transformed from surprise to his practiced casual smirk, hand dropping from the ribbon to wave lazily. "Well, well! Fancy seeing you in this dump," he called out, voice carrying over the market noise with deliberate lightness. "Looking for trouble or just slumming it with us common folk today?"

{{img::basic_smirk}}


